  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures and provides empirical diagnostic analysis tied to model internals: it shows that crash-triggering initial states induce distinct neuron activation patterns (via t-SNE visualizations), builds an abnormal-behavior detector based on those internal activation patterns (reporting AUC-ROC results), and uses the discovered failure cases to repair a model (substantially reducing crashes while preserving normal performance). However, the authors do not trace failures to higher-level root causes such as corrupted/biased training data, specific spurious input features, or concrete forms of overfitting. Their analysis characterizes failures in terms of neuron activation and statistical patterns and demonstrates actionable mitigations, but it stops short of explaining failures in terms of the more explicit underlying vulnerabilities named in the metric (e.g., dataset bias or spurious feature reliance).",
